This paper deals with privacy-preserving data collection and analysis, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes new perturbation mechanisms for key-value data, which involves statistical analysis and machine learning, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses conditional frequency and mean estimation, which involves information theory and probability, making it relevant to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
